2.5. Mockup & Other Notes

  


Requirements

General Notes:

  * Saving the order after generating truss print requests would trigger the real-time alert for the designer (see corresponding notes).
  * Note that if a change is made to the order that affects the trusses, or a change is made to a truss, the salesperson will need to request a new print (using the checkbox column). Clicking the Generate Request checkbox will override any existing request for the selected row (move it to Archive).

Development Specification

Dev Specs:

  * Use a Virtual RG for the View/Edit Truss Prints, with MRG controls that update the underlying RG.
  * Use an AppHosting.zone setting that is an Order-level memo expression that pulls information into a memo for display.
  * Use editable expressions for these fields so that we can put them in the MRG but keep them out of the RG (I think). If not, we may need to simply push these fields out past the end of the RG. From what Matthias knows of ClientScope, this should work fine.
  * For the read-only version of the sketch, the sketchpad would either attach the image on the Sketch record and use ArchivedDocumentImage or it would save the data URL, then use DataUrlToImage.
  * The "View Print" will need to use MemoLinksInText to generate a URL for the archived document. This will need to have some hardcoding for the URL format. For example:



Assign vMemoLink = PipeListItem( MemoLinksInText( OrderTrussPrints), 1);

Assign vFileName = RightOf( vMemoLink, ":");

If( HasPrefix( vMemoLink, "File:")

 , AbsoluteWebUrl( "/Detail/Documents/" +

 EncodeURL( vFileName) +

 "?RecordID=_Orders%09%09" +

 String( LookupRecordNum) +

 "&"

 )

 , ''

 )

  * Consider [[PC0135350]] - Generic Generic AppHosting Framework for Storing Files in S3
